Fixes #149
Build passing: https://travis-ci.org/anishkny/realworld/builds/300826986#L421

Just to see what it could look like
Would close #150

This PR includes just the code so that TravisCI can run daily and send out PRs in case the README changes. Here is what the generated README would look like:
https://github.com/anishkny/realworld/blob/updated-readme/README.md
Note that WIP sections are now auto-generated also based on querying issues in the main repo. E.g.:
https://github.com/gothinkster/realworld/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3Abackend+label%3Awip

"reponsible" --> "responsible"
"All WIP stacks that are a WIP are experimental and incomplete." --> "All WIP stacks are experimental and incomplete."
"continuously helping push the project" --> "who are continuously helping push the project"
"who have helped contributed to RealWorld" --> "who have contributed to RealWorld"
Also, error out if GH_TOKEN is not present

Running the API Postman collection should be more robust now. Try:
./api/run-api-tests.sh
Closes #202
I fixed an assertion description where it should say ... is false instead of ... is true.
After discussions in the Ember community we've decided to merge the "Ember Octane Realworld" app into the regular Ember Realworld app so there is no longer a need for both anymore.
This PR address #527
For reference: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Lists_of_common_misspellings/For_machines
The url is obsolete because master branch has been renamed to main some time ago
To register a new user POST to /users not to /user.

Closes #518
@Weedshaker I've created this PR to close your issue and add the repo/project to the README.
Have a look and let me know if you have any comments or questions.
Once the PR is merged, the repo would appear in the README within 24 hours as it is auto-generated :)
Add Android(Kotlin) example project link please review and merge into the master repo.

update contributing.md
add github templates
related to #663

This is exactly the same as the previous test with login,
but this time without login.
This catches some JSON serialization errors that I had observed in a
backend implementation.

Previously we had newman": "^3.5.2", but if you install exactly 3.5.2
e.g. with npm install newman@3.5.2 the ./api/run-api-tests.sh fails with:
Unrecognized arguments: --global-var
because that feature was added after 3.5. It works with npm install
because if fetches the newer version currently 3.10 which has it.
Since I was upgrading this, I though I might as well update to 5 as it just
works.
